'''Víctor Muñoz Villanueva''' (born 13 July 2003) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] or [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[La Liga]] club [[CA Osasuna|Osasuna]] and the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]], Muñoz joined [[FC Barcelona]]'s [[La Masia]] at the age of eleven, after starting it out at [[CE Sant Gabriel]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.relevo.com/futbol/liga-primera/victor-munoz-avion-castilla-raul-20241025123519-nt.html|title=El "avión" del Castilla de Raúl que creció junto a Fermín y Balde en La Masia: "Que te echen del Barça genera resquemor y el Madrid aprovechó..."|trans-title=Raúl's "Castilla plane" that grew up with Fermín and Balde in La Masia: "Being kicked out of Barça generates resentment and Madrid took advantage..."|language=es|website=[[Relevo]]|publisher=[[Grupo Vocento]]|date=25 October 2024|access-date=18 January 2025}}</ref> In 2017, at the age of fourteen, he left the club and joined the youth academy of [[CF Damm]].{{Citation needed|date=April 2026}}

===Real Madrid===
In June 2021, Muñoz joined the youth teams of [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/2021/06/26/primera/1624716050_096646.html|title=El Madrid se hace con una joya del DAMM con pasado azulgrana|trans-title=Madrid get a pearl from Damm with a blue-and-red past|publisher=[[Diario AS]]|language=es|date=26 June 2021|accessdate=22 July 2025}}</ref> where he played in the [[UEFA Youth League]]. After making his senior debut with [[farm team]] [[RSC Internacional FC]] in 2022, he was promoted to the club's [[Real Madrid Castilla|reserve team]] in [[Primera Federación]] in the following year.{{Citation needed|date=April 2026}}

During the [[2024–25 Primera Federación|2024–25 season]], Muñoz was regarded to have established himself as a starter for Castilla.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://okdiario.com/diariomadridista/real-madrid/ser-descartado-barcelona-ser-convocado-ancelotti-historia-victor-munoz-486516|title=De ser descartado por el Barcelona a ser convocado por Ancelotti: la historia de Víctor Muñoz|trans-title=From being discarded by Barcelona to being called up by Ancelotti: the story of Víctor Muñoz|language=es|website=[[Okdiario]]|date=13 December 2024|access-date=18 January 2025}}</ref> On 11 May 2025, he made his La Liga debut, substituting [[Vinícius Júnior]] in [[El Clásico]] match against former side Barcelona which ended in a 4–3 away defeat.<ref>{{cite web |last=Brotherton |first=Alex |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c62x2g9d9dgt |title=Barcelona 4–3 Real Madrid|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=11 May 2025 }}</ref>

On 18 June 2025, Muñoz made his [[FIFA Club World Cup]] debut in Real Madrid's first match under new head coach [[Xabi Alonso]], coming on in the 80th minute for Vinícius Júnior in a 1–1 draw against [[Al Hilal SFC|Al Hilal]].<ref>{{Cite web|first=Steve|last=Sutcliffe|title=Real Madrid held by Al-Hilal on Alexander-Arnold debut|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/sports/soccer/real-madrid-held-by-al-hilal-on-alexander-arnold-debut/ar-AA1GZ59U?ocid=BingNewsVerp|website=[[MSN]]|date=18 June 2025|access-date=20 June 2025}}</ref>

===Osasuna===
On 11 July 2025, Muñoz signed a five-year contract with fellow top-tier club [[CA Osasuna]], for a transfer fee of €5 million for 50% of his economic rights, with a further €1 million due in variables.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.osasuna.es/news/read/36628/el-club-atletico-osasuna-ficha-a-victor-munoz-para-las-proximas-cinco-temporadas|title=El Club Atlético Osasuna ficha a Víctor Muñoz para las próximas cinco temporadas|trans-title=Club Atlético Osasuna sign Víctor Muñoz for the following five seasons|publisher=CA Osasuna|language=es|date=11 July 2025|access-date=22 July 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
On 27 March 2026, Muñoz made his debut for [[Spain national football team|Spain]] and scored its third goal in a 3–0 friendly victory against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] at [[Estadio de la Ceramica]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/401865041 |title=Rodri returns, Oyarzabal nets brace as Spain beat Serbia|publisher=[[ESPN]]|date=27 March 2026 }}</ref>

==Style of play==
Muñoz plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] or [[Forward (association football)|forward]]. American news website ''[[The Sporting News]]'' wrote in 2024 that "his speed is what makes him stand out the most and made him recently known as the fastest player in the Real Madrid squad".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us-es/futbol/real-madrid/news/victor-munoz-real-madrid-delantero-rechazado-barcelona/602e5253f302a9b49621b175|title=Rechazado por el Barcelona y convocado por Ancelotti: quién es Víctor Muñoz, el delantero del Real Madrid|trans-title=Rejected by Barcelona and called up by Ancelotti: who is Víctor Muñoz, the Real Madrid striker?|language=es|website=[[The Sporting News]]|publisher=Sporting News Holdings|date=13 December 2024|access-date=18 January 2025}}</ref>

